summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Hannah is seeing a new guy, but her attentions are diverted by Adam, Marnie and her new roommate.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. Hannah tries to start fresh by dating a brand new guy and throwing a housewarming party with brand new roommate Elijah, but it's hard to move on when she's still playing nurse to Adam. Marnie gets some bad news at work and a visit from her mom, Shoshanna avoids Ray at the party, and sun-kissed Jessa returns from her honeymoon.

summaries.short: Hannah finds she's the subject of Adam's hate-album and tries to keep an open mind about her new boyfriend's politics.
summaries.full: Hannah gets some unsolicited musical attention from heartbroken Adam and some displeasing opinions on her writing from Sandy (Donald Glover). Elijah questions his sexuality; Marnie makes a career compromise when her curatorial dreams are crushed; Jessa revels in married life; Shoshanna and Ray make magic; Elijah and Marnie harbor a secret.

summaries.short: Season 1 finale. Jessa throws a mystery party where the girls realize their dreams are not what they imagined.
summaries.full: Season One finale. Hannah starts to question her relationship with Adam; Jessa throws a mystery party where Marnie embraces her free-spirited side, and Shoshanna's uniqueness works in her favor.

summaries.short: Hannah plays hard to work hard; Marnie re-meets Booth Jonathan; Elijah accidentally opens up to Hannah.
summaries.full: On a freelance writing assignment to get out of her comfort zone, Hannah befriends the junkie downstairs and parties hard with Elijah, who reveals an explosive secret. Meanwhile, Marnie has a long awaited run-in with artist Booth Jonathan (Jorma Taccone).

summaries.short: Hannah decides to take some chances after colliding with Marnie over rent money and seeing a former classmate get published.
summaries.full: Behind on rent and resentful of the literary success of a former classmate (Jenny Slate), Hannah starts work at Grumpy Cafe and does a reading hosted by a former professor (Michael Imperioli). Marnie finds it increasingly difficult to support Hannah financially and emotionally. Jessa is confronted by her former boss, and Shoshanna goes on a day date with an online match.
